---
import CodeBlock from "../../../components/common/CodeBlock";
import BlogLayout from "../../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro";

// Metadata
const title = "Objects in C - Christopher Villamarín Projects";
const description =
  "Explore how to implement object-oriented programming in C based on the book 'Object-oriented Programming with ANSI-C' by Axel-Tobias Schreiner. Learn about encapsulation, classes, and efficient memory management.";
const keywords = [
  "Objects in C",
  "object-oriented programming",
  "ANSI-C",
  "encapsulation",
  "classes in C",
  "development in C",
  "Christopher Villamarín",
  "xeland314",
  "projects",
  "Ecuador",
].join(", ");
const authors = "Christopher Alexander Villamarín Pila";
const ogTitle = "Objects in C - Project by Christopher Villamarín";
const ogDescription =
  "Discover how to implement object-oriented programming in C with practical examples. Based on the book 'Object-oriented Programming with ANSI-C'.";
const ogUrl = "https://xeland314.github.io/en/blog/objects-in-c/";
const ogImage = "https://xeland314.github.io/images/objects_in_c_preview.png";
const imageAlt = "Preview of the Objects in C project";
const canonicalUrl = "https://xeland314.github.io/en/blogs/objects-in-c/";
const robots = "index, follow";
---

<BlogLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  keywords={keywords}
  author={authors}
  applicationName="Objects in C"
  url={ogUrl}
  image={ogImage}
  imageAlt={imageAlt}
  canonical={canonicalUrl}
  robots={robots}
  lang="en"
  isAutomaticTranslation={true}
  pubDate={new Date("2023-03-18")}
  githubLink="https://github.com/xeland314/objects-in-C"
>
  <div class="p-0 sm:p-0">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <p class="text-lg">
        Based on the book{" "}
        <a
          href="https://www.freetechbooks.com/object-oriented-programming-with-ansi-c-t551.html#:~:text=Object%2Doriented%20Programming%20with%20Ansi%2DC&text=Uses%20ANSI%2DC%20to%20discover,program%20to%20catch%20mistakes%20earlier."
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
        >
          Object-oriented Programming with Ansi-C
        </a>{" "}
        by Axel-Tobias Schreiner.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Encapsulation</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        A base <code>struct</code> called <code>Class</code> is defined. From this,
        more objects can be created that inherit the same attributes and methods.
        The design allows for efficient reuse and management of attributes.
      </p>
      <CodeBlock
        code={`typedef struct {
    size_t size;
    void * (* ctor) (void * self, va_list * app);
    void * (* dtor) (void * self);
    void * (* clone) (const void * self);
    size_t (* sizeOf) (const void * self);
    int (* differ) (const void * self, const void * other);
    char * (* toString) (const void * self);
} Class;
/* Overloaded methods: */
void * new(const void * _class, ...);
void delete(void * self);
void * clone(const void * self);
int differ(const void * self, const void * other);
size_t sizeOf(const void * self);
char * toString(const void * self);`}
        language="c"
        client:visible
      />
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Using the repository</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Object management simplifies memory management in C. Consider the
        example of initializing a string using the <code>String</code> class:
      </p>
      <CodeBlock
        code={`#include "String.h"
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    void * text = new(String, "Hello world");
    printf("%s", toString(text));
    return 0;
}`}
        language="c"
        client:visible
      />
      <p class="mt-4">
        This approach hides memory management in the background, making the code
        cleaner and more readable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Main functions</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-4">
        <li>
          <strong>Constructor:</strong> Initializes any object in a standardized way
          with <code>new()</code>. For example:
          <CodeBlock
            code={`void * text = new(String, "Hello, world");`}
            language="c"
            client:visible
          />
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloner:</strong> Creates an independent copy of the object:
          <CodeBlock
            code="void * textCopy = clone(text);"
            language="c"
            client:visible
          />
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Destructor:</strong> Frees the object's memory using:
          <CodeBlock code="delete(text);" language="c" client:visible />
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>toString:</strong> Returns the object's content as a printable string:
          <CodeBlock
            code={`printf("text = %s\\n", toString(text));`}
            language="c"
            client:visible
          />
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Usage examples</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        To compile the examples and see the results in the console, use the
        commands:
      </p>
      <CodeBlock
        code="make examples && make run_examples"
        language="sh"
        client:visible
      />
      <p class="mt-4">
        The example code is in the <code>examples</code> folder.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Tests</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        To verify the integrity of the implemented functions, you can run the
        tests with:
      </p>
      <CodeBlock code="make tests" client:visible />
      <p class="mt-4">
        The tests use the{" "}
        <a
          href="https://github.com/mity/acutest"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
        >
          acutest.h
        </a>{" "}
        library. This allows adding more functionalities and testing them.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Cleanup</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">To remove all compiled files, use the command:</p>
      <CodeBlock code="make clean" client:visible />
    </section>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
